                    <chunk name="param_input" index="2">
                      <items count="7">
                        <item name="Description" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">Continuity handling at extraordinary vertices:
0) None - The NURBS patches are used as is.
1) G1 -  The NURBS patches are modified so they are G1 at the extraordinary vertex.
2) G2 -  The NURBS patches are modified so they are G2 at the extraordinary vertex.
3) G1x -  The NURBS patches are modified so they are G1 at the extraordinary vertex and tend to be closer to G1 along edges near the extraordinary vertex.
4) G1xx -  The NURBS patches are modified so they are G1 at the extraordinary vertex and G1 along edges near the extraordinary vertex.
</item>
